# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for the AI Word Editing Workflow
# =============================================================================
# This workflow produces several files that should not be committed to git:
#   - The Word document itself and dated backup copies
#   - Pandoc Markdown exports of the document (lossy, regenerated each session)
#   - Word lock files
#
# The guide files (AGENTS.md, README.md, GRAMMATICAL_RULES_FORWARD.md,
# ITEMS_TO_CHECK.md, AI_ERRORS_TO_AVOID.md, WRITING_LESSONS_LEARNED.md,
# AI_WRITING_INDICATORS.md) are explicitly NOT ignored — they ARE the repo.
# =============================================================================

# Word documents (originals and dated backups)
*.docx
*.doc
*.docm
*.dotx
*.dotm

# Word lock / temporary files
~$*
*.tmp

# Pandoc Markdown exports of the Word document.
# The guide files above use .md too, so we cannot blanket-ignore *.md.
# Add your specific document export filename(s) below to keep them out of git:
#
# MyDocument.md
# MyReport.md

# Media folder created by pandoc when it extracts embedded images
media/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo

# Lesson-import staging folders (not committed; contents are merged into guide files)
Files_From_Using_Tool_*/
